==English==
===Etymology===
[[back formation]] from ''[[disgruntle]]''
===Adjective===
'''gruntled'''
# (''jocular'') [[satisfied]].
#: 1938: ''He spoke with a certain what-is-it in his voice, and I could see that, if not actually disgruntled, he was far from being gruntled.'' &mdash; [[w:P. G. Wodehouse|P. G. Wodehouse]], ''[[w:The Code of the Woosters|The Code of the Woosters]]''
===Usage notes===
''[[gruntle|Gruntle]]'' is today considered obsolete and is not in normal usage.  ''Gruntled'' is used only [[humorous|humorously]] as the imagined [[opposite]] of [[disgruntled]].
===Antonyms===
* [[disgruntled]]